			</classificationInformation>
			<CASNumber>NA</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">A cation exchange resin is an insoluble polymer with positively charged functional groups that exchange pollutant cations with less objectionable ones. It is used in ion exchange systems to remove cationic impurities, such as calcium and magnesium ions in hard water, by exchanging them with sodium or potassium ions. The resin undergoes regeneration to recharge with new sodium ions after full ion exchange. Cation exchange resins are distinct from anion exchange resins, which remove negatively charged ions.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">阳离子交换树脂是一种不溶性聚合物，具有带正电的官能团，可以将污染物阳离子与不太令人反感的阳离子交换。它用于离子交换系统，通过与钠或钾离子交换来去除阳离子杂质，如硬水中的钙和镁离子。树脂经过再生，在完全离子交换后用新的钠离子重新充电。阳离子交换树脂不同于阴离子交换树脂，后者可以去除带负电的离子。</common:generalComment>
